Diagnosis. Assigned to the genus
Limnonectes
on the basis of molecular evidence (
Fig. 3
), the presence of fanglike odontoid processes on the lower jaw (
Emerson et al. 2000
;
Lambertz et al . 2014
), and males with hypertrophied heads (
Lambertz et al . 2014
). A small-sized
Limnonectes
having males with SVL 30.5 –42.0, females with SVL 32.9–37.9 ; males with low-profiled, U-shaped caruncle with free posterior margin that completely occupies, but does not extend beyond, interobital region; males with hypertrophied heads; both sexes with enlarged odontoid processes on anterior margin of lower jaw; and webbing on toes.
